This folder contains tablulated results for full model atmosphere solutions. The three currently supported families are Allard(1999), Kurucz(1991), and Castelli & Kurucz 2003.

***Note that the code does not check these tables for consistency, so care must be taken to use the correct metallicity for the run.*** Also note that the mixture is fixed, and changes in surface metallicity over the run, from effects like microscopic diffusion, are not accounted for.

For Allard, the code only supports solar metallicity tables, although AMES-Condu2 has data for other mixtures. The recommended table is Nextgen2.all; AMES-Cond2.all and Ames-Dusty2.all are also supported, and represent different treatments of dust in very cool atmospheres.

For Kurucz, there are different tables for different metallicities; the assumed [Fe/H] is at the start of the header, and the file names include a shorthand for metallicity (atmk1990m10.tab is for [Fe/H] of minus 1.0; atmk1990p05.tab is for [Fe/H]=+0.5 and so forth. Scripts can be used to interpolate between tables for metallicities not in the folder.  